 and uptake of circulating amines, caution is advised.', 'Antagonism', 'Minoxidil, Deoxycholic acid, Calcium gluconate, Pimecrolimus, Magnesium sulfate, Aminobenzoic acid, Finasteride, Ivermectin, Caffeine, Diclofenac, Cromoglicic acid, More', 'Citalopram, Duloxetine, Vilazodone, Sertraline, Paroxetine, Desvenlafaxine, Fluoxetine, Oxitriptan, Viloxazine, Milnacipran, Vortioxetine, More', 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/48441/', '[1] "Product Information. Mirvaso (brimonidine topical)." Galderma Laboratories Inc, Cranbury, NJ.[2] "Product Information. Alphagan (brimonidine ophthalmic)." Allergan Inc, Irvine, CA.', 1767369485);
